badge.name: Badge
badge.description: A badge is an indicator or label that provides additional information about a specific element or action. It's often used to highlight important details, provide contextual clues, or convey status updates.

button.name: Button
button.description: A button is a visual element that allows users to trigger an action or event with a single click. It's often used for calls-to-action, navigation, or form submission.

input.name: Input
input.description: An input is a user interface element that allows users to enter and edit text-based information, such as names, addresses, or comments. It's a fundamental component of forms and interactive content, facilitating data input and user interactions.

Divider.name: Divider

accordion-item.description: An accordion item is a section of content within an accordion that can be expanded and collapsed. It's often used for navigation, filtering, or other tasks.

card-header.name: Card header
card-header.description: A card header is a visual element that provides context and information about the content within a card. It can include titles, subtitles, or other metadata.

login-sections.name: Login sections
login-sections.description: A login section is an interactive element that allows users to log in to a system. It can include forms, buttons, or other interactive elements.

signup-sections.name: Signup sections
signup-sections.description: A signup section is an interactive element that allows users to sign up for a system. It can include forms, buttons, or other interactive elements.

avatar.name: Avatar
avatar.description: An avatar is a visual representation of a user's identity or profile. It can be used to represent the user in various contexts, such as chat windows or profiles.

avatar-labeled.name: Avatar labeled
avatar-labeled.description: An avatar labeled is a visual representation of a user's identity or profile that includes additional information, such as name or email address.

avatar-stack.name: Avatar stack
avatar-stack.description: An avatar stack is an interactive element that allows users to view multiple avatars in a compact format. It's often used for displaying profiles or contact information.

checklist-item.name: Checklist Item
checklist-item.description: A checklist item is a task or an item that needs to be completed or checked off a list. It's commonly used in to-do lists, project management tools, or any situation where a list of items needs to be tracked.

table-cell.name: Table cell
table-cell.description: A table cell is a single unit within a table that holds data or information. It's used to organize and present tabular data in a structured format, allowing users to easily read and interpret the information.

table.name: Table
table.description: A table is a structured format used to organize and present data in rows and columns. It allows users to easily read, compare, and interpret information, making it an essential component for displaying tabular data in applications.

other-icons.name: Other icons
other-icons.description: icon collection featuring various categories including social media, payment methods, browsers, operating systems, design tools, and development environments. Each icon is carefully crafted to maintain consistent visual quality while representing well-known brands and applications. Use these icons to enhance user recognition and provide familiar visual references in your interfaces.

project-switch.name: Project Switch
project-switch.description: A project switch is an interactive element that allows users to easily toggle between different projects or contexts within an application. It enhances user experience by providing quick access to various project settings or views.

view-mode-picker.name: View Mode Picker
view-mode-picker.description: A view mode picker is an interactive element that enables users to select different display modes for content. It allows users to switch between various layouts or perspectives, enhancing the flexibility and usability of the interface.

drop-down-list.name: Drop-Down List
drop-down-list.description: A drop-down list is an interactive element that presents a list of options for users to choose from. It allows for efficient selection of a single option from a predefined set, commonly used in forms and navigation menus.

date-picker.name: Date Picker
date-picker.description: A date picker is an interactive element that allows users to select a date from a calendar interface. It simplifies the process of date selection, ensuring accuracy and enhancing user experience in forms and scheduling applications.

color-picker.name: Color Picker
color-picker.description: A color picker is an interactive element that allows users to select a color from a palette or spectrum. It provides a visual interface for choosing colors, enhancing the customization and design capabilities within applications.

ai-shortcuts.name: AI Shortcuts
ai-shortcuts.description: AI Shortcuts are icon-only or icon-plus-text elements designed to guide users to the main features of the application. They provide quick access to essential functionalities, enhancing user navigation and improving overall efficiency in utilizing the application's capabilities.

ai-shortcuts-item.name: AI Shortcuts Item
ai-shortcuts-item.description: AI Shortcuts are icon-only or icon-plus-text elements designed to guide users to the main features of the application. They provide quick access to essential functionalities, enhancing user navigation and improving overall efficiency in utilizing the application's capabilities.

featured-icon.name: Featured Icon
featured-icon.description: A featured icon is a visual element that is placed on a round or square-shaped background, available in various themed styles. It serves to highlight important features or actions within an application, enhancing visual appeal and user engagement.

menu-list-item.name: Menu List Item
menu-list-item.description: A menu list item is a text link that can include an optional icon as a lead. It serves as a navigational element within a menu, allowing users to easily access different sections or features of the application, enhancing usability and organization.

product-card-horizontal.name: Product Card Horizontal
product-card-horizontal.description: A product card horizontal is a visual element designed to showcase product information in a horizontal layout. It typically includes an image, product title, description, and pricing details, making it ideal for displaying multiple products side by side in a compact format. This layout enhances user engagement by providing a clear and organized view of product offerings.

product-card-vertical.name: Product Card Vertical
product-card-vertical.description: A product card vertical is a visual element designed to present product information in a vertical layout. It usually features an image, product title, description, and pricing details, allowing for a more detailed view of each product. This layout is particularly effective for showcasing individual products in a list or grid format, enhancing the user's ability to browse and compare options.

drop-down-button.name: Drop-Down Button
drop-down-button.description: The Drop-Down Button is an interactive element that reveals a list of options when clicked. It allows users to select from multiple choices in a compact format, enhancing the user experience by providing a clean and organized way to navigate through various actions or settings within the application.

image-editor.name: Image Editor
image-editor.description: The Image Editor is a powerful tool that allows users to manipulate and enhance images directly within the application. It provides a range of features such as cropping, resizing, filtering, and adjusting colors, enabling users to create visually appealing graphics tailored to their needs.

image-editor-/-toolbar.name: Image Editor / Toolbar
image-editor-/-toolbar.description: The Image Editor Toolbar is a user-friendly interface that houses essential tools and options for editing images. It includes icons for common actions like undo, redo, crop, and apply filters, allowing users to access editing functionalities quickly and efficiently while working on their images.

markdown-editor.name: Markdown Editor
markdown-editor.description: The Markdown Editor is a user-friendly tool for creating and formatting text using Markdown syntax. It features live preview and syntax highlighting, making it easy for writers and developers to produce well-structured content efficiently. Ideal for documentation, blogging, and note-taking, it streamlines the writing process.
